$grp PS_MissionDescription : "{3136BE42592F3B1B}PrefabsEditable/MissionDescription/EditableMissionDescription.et" {
 SUM {
  coords 3750.24 0 11666.629
  m_sTitle "Summary"
  m_sTextData "Radical environmentalist from the Earth Contamination Outfit have launched a surprise attack on a TEM POWER oil rig off the coast of Scotland."\
  "They've captured hostages and plan to blow the rig sky high with the goal of causing an environmental distaster."\
  ""\
  "Can 42Cmdo rapidly deploy and neutralize the threat in time?"\
  "__________________________________"\
  "• RATIO: 2.7:1:0.4 - UK:ECO:CIV"\
  "• JIP: Blufor - Yes | Opfor - Deny after 5mins."\
  "• Timelimit: 35mins."\
  "• There is no single commander for ECO. It's competely decentralised."\
  ""\
  "- THIS MISSION HAS NOT BEEN DESIGNED FOR ADDITONAL SLOTS TO BE ADDED"
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
 }
 NOTES {
  coords 3818.963 0 11762.15
  m_sTitle "Mission notes"
  m_sTextData "THIS MISSION HAS NOT BEEN DESIGNED FOR ADDITIONAL SLOTS TO BE ADDED"\
  ""\
  "<h2>END CONDITIONS</h2>"\
  "<b>UK:</b>  "\
  "• <b>Major Victory</b> – Defuse the bomb, eliminate 90% of ECO forces, and ensure at least 50% of the hostages remain alive by the time 90% of ECO are neutralized.  "\
  "• <b>Minor Victory</b> – Defuse the bomb and eliminate 90% of ECO forces, but 50% of the hostages are dead by the time ECO is neutralized.  "\
  "• <b>Pyrrhic Victory</b> – The bomb is defused, but at least 87% of UK forces are killed in the process."\
  ""\
  "<b>ECO:</b>  "\
  "• <b>Major Victory</b> – Successfully defend the bomb for 35 minutes, allowing it to detonate and destroy the rig, killing everyone onboard.  "\
  "<b>OR</b>  "\
  "Eliminate 87% of UK ground troops, allowing the bomb to detonate uncontested.  "\
  ""\
  "• <b>Minor Victory</b> – The bomb is defused, but ECO successfully kills 87% of UK forces, allowing ECO to escape and potentially strike again."\
  ""\
  "<h2>MISC</h2>"\
  "• RATIO: 2.7 : 1 : 0.4 — UK : ECO : CIV  "\
  "• Time limit: 35 minutes  "\
  "• JIP: BLUFOR – Yes | OPFOR – Denied after 5 minutes  "\
  "• AO Limit: Yes – ECO team"\
  ""\
  "<h2>HOSTAGE GAMEPLAY</h2>"\
  "• Hostages cannot be placed in access routes to buildings or key areas.  "\
  "• Hostages cannot be used in exploitative ways, such as being climbed on or positioned to create blatantly unfair gameplay advantages.  "\
  "• Hostages may not be executed by the ECO team UNLESS..(see below)"\
  ""\
  "<b>EXCEPTIONS:</b>  "\
  "• If the bomb is defused, hostages are no longer considered strategically valuable. ECO may then decide how to deal with them.  "\
  "• If a hostage is actively or repeatedly disobeying orders, attempting to escape, attempting deception, or assisting the UK team, ECO may administer punishment, including execution."\
  ""\
  "<h2>PERFORMANCE</h2>"\
  "Performance on this rig is generally higher than typical Arma 3 environments. However, during nighttime conditions, lighting may reduce FPS due to multiple dynamic shadows cast by lamps and floodlights around the structure. This effect is amplified during heavy rain."\
  ""\
  "This is most noticeable near the center of the rig where the large floodlights illuminate the tower, gangways, and chain-lined fences, creating complex shadow interactions."\
  ""\
  "If performance becomes an issue, consider lowering shadow or lighting quality in your graphics settings to improve FPS."\
  "(In testing at maximum graphics settings, performance remained above 45 FPS in the central area at night.)"\
  ""\
  "If performance becomes unplayable, a Game Master may adjust the time of day or weather conditions to something similar but less demanding. Use discretion when making such changes."
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 6
 }
 CL {
  coords 3818.963 0 11762.15
  m_sTitle "Changelog"
  m_sTextData "V4"\
  "Added: "\
  "• BLUFOR drone operator"\
  "• New pictures of the rig with northern headings added"\
  "• Picture of the bomb"\
  ""\
  "Fixed:"\
  "• OPFOR marksman missing weapon and low ammo"\
  ""\
  "Updated:"\
  "• All briefing have had a pass to better refine them and add HTML formatting and styles."
  m_bEmptyFactionVisibility 1
  m_bShowForAnyFaction 1
  m_iOrder 6
 }
}